<collectingCountry box="[455,556,1218,1244]" name="Armenia" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[567,642,1218,1244]" name="Russia" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Russia</collectingCountry>
(Siberia, 
<collectingRegion box="[753,855,1218,1244]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[876,940,1219,1245]" name="Japan" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[955,1070,1218,1244]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, Etorofu Is., Kunashiri Is.) (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="179 - 197" refId="ref76388" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 b) Pamphilius stramineipes (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) and its close relatives. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 14, 179 - 197." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara 1988b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S." box="[319,594,1254,1280]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="62 - 119" refId="ref79983" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S. (2012) Podotryad Symphyta - Sidyachebryukhie. In: Lelej, A. S. (Ed), Annotated Catalogue of the Insects of Russian Far East. Vol. I. Hymenoptera. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, pp. 62 - 119. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2012">Sundukov &amp; Lelej 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,1437,1146,1749]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1290,1316]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Host plant</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[336,446,1291,1317]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[456,564,1291,1317]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[456,512,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Rosa</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, H." box="[577,699,1290,1316]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="293 - 302" refId="ref73428" refString="Hara, H. (1993) Life history of a leaf-rolling sawfly, Pamphilius stramineipes (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae), in Hokkaido. Japanese Journal of Entomology, 61, 293 - 302." type="journal article" year="1993">Hara 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H." box="[709,978,1290,1317]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="272 - 276" refId="ref77731" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H. (2005) Pamphiliidae. In: Aoki, T. et al., Insect Larvae of Japan. Gakken, Tokyo, pp. 272 - 276. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="2005">Shinohara &amp; Hara 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Records of other plants in Europe (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Crataegus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[238,341,1327,1352]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Fragaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[238,341,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Fragaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[355,425,1326,1352]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[355,425,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Rubus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[479,621,1326,1352]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sanguisorba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[479,621,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Sanguisorba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A. &amp; Altenhofer, E. &amp; Blank, S. M. &amp; Jansen, E. &amp; Kraus, M. &amp; Pschorn-Walcher, H. &amp; Ritzau, C." box="[677,880,1326,1353]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="49 - 135" refId="ref80046" refString="Taeger, A., Altenhofer, E., Blank, S. M., Jansen, E., Kraus, M., Pschorn-Walcher, H. &amp; Ritzau, C. (1998) Kommentare zur Biologie, Verbreitung und Gefahrdung der Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). In: Taeger, A. &amp; Blank, S. M. (Eds), Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern, pp. 49 - 135." type="book chapter" year="1998">
Taeger 
<emphasis box="[760,816,1326,1352]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
) need confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,1437,1146,1749]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1362,1388]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[633,804,1363,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[633,804,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[988,1159,1363,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[988,1159,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[1351,1437,1362,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[1351,1437,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[232,430,1398,1424]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[450,660,1398,1424]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[773,944,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[773,944,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kontuniemi" authorityYear="1946" box="[959,1097,1398,1424]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thorwaldi">
<emphasis box="[959,1097,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. thorwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1154,1278,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1278,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complexes in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[193,365,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[193,365,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup, while our molecular analyses did not indicate a close relationship among the three species complexes. In our COI analysis (
<figureCitation box="[602,699,1470,1497]" captionStart="FIGURE 151" captionStartId="238.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[163,1422,186,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-26@238.[157,1430,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="238" captionText="FIGURE 151. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 4." pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Fig. 151</figureCitation>
), the 
<specimenCount box="[758,937,1470,1496]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[972,1142,1471,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[972,1142,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1208,1272,1471,1497]" name="Japan" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1376,1470,1496]" name="Italy" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Italy</collectingCountry>
were retrieved as a monophyletic group (with 93% UFBoot support), which was sister (with 100% UFBoot support) to the clade of 
<specimenCount box="[286,437,1542,1568]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" type="generic">26 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[473,605,1542,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortorum">
<emphasis box="[473,605,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. hortorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the NaK analysis (
<figureCitation box="[852,949,1542,1568]" captionStart="FIGURE 161" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1403,189,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@246.[171,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 161. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Fig. 161</figureCitation>
), the two sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[1206,1376,1543,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[1206,1376,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,215,1579,1605]" name="Japan" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Japan</collectingCountry>
formed a clade with 100% UFBoot support. This clade then came close to 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1181,1578,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="togashii">
<emphasis box="[1063,1181,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. togashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1998" box="[1236,1429,1578,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heecheonparki">
<emphasis box="[1236,1429,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">P. heecheonparki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this relationship had low UFBoot supports of 42 and 58%.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="94.[151,1437,1146,1749]" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[199,478,1650,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[199,478,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Pamphilius stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Palaearctic species widely spread from western Europe through Siberia and Sakhalin to 
<collectingRegion box="[257,370,1686,1712]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[382,449,1687,1713]" name="Japan" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Japan</collectingCountry>
. However, there are no collection records from other areas of the Russian Far East (e.g., Primorskij Kraj) and 
<collectingCountry box="[390,462,1723,1749]" name="South Korea" pageId="94" pageNumber="95">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
